b'     INDIAN INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY MADRAS  Academic Section      Circular No. 22A/JM2016/B2/2016 &nbs;p;&nbsp;&nbs;p;&nbsp;&nbs;p;Dated 19.04.2016    Dear Students,    &nbs;p;  Sub: Teacher Course Feedback (TCF)  Procedure to be followed  reg.    TCF period  19 th  April 2016 to 26 th  April 2016  It is the responsibility of the students to provide Teacher Course Feedback (TCF) for each of the courses that they have credited. This provides valuable feedback to course faculty as well as to the Institute. The TCF of JanMay 2016 semester will be sought online through academic section portal.  Please follow the steps mentioned below:</p  Access    and login using your LDAP user id and password Click on TCF form from the menu on the left hand side The courses you have credited will be populated with the name of the instructor Select each course to fill the TCF form for that course  In case of courses with multiple teachers handling a course, choose the instructor(s) who is/are handling the course.    TCF portal will be open from 19.0.2016 to 26.04.2016.    Please make sure that you complete the process within this duration.    Sd/  Deputy Registrar (Courses)    To  All Students through  students@list.iitm.ac.in   '

